  "text": "). Images were biascorrected and classified into gray matter, white matter, cerebrospinal fluid and non-brain tissue using Diffeomorphic Anatomical Registration through Exponentiated Lie algebra (DARTEL) registration toolbox [CITATION_1] . Data were segmented based on tissue probability maps, indexing the prior probability of any voxel in a registered image being grey or white matter or cerebrospinal fluid. An average template from the data was created, to which the images were registered. Additionally, the images were affine-transformed to MNI space and smoothed with a 6-mm FWHM kernel. Total intracranial volume was calculated by adding the tissue probabilities of gray matter, white matter and cerebrospinal fluid and used as a covariate. For group statistics of gray matter images, the same analysis as with the functional images was performed while additionally controlling for total intracranial volume. In order to control for the influence of gray matter differences, brain volume was extracted using anatomical masks comprising the caudate, the putamen and the amygdala derived from the WFU PickAtlas v2.4 [CITATION_2] and separately added as an additional covariate.",
